\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 What The Background Check Does Not Do\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 This is as important as what it does.\
The background check does not guarantee future behavior. A sophisticated bad actor with patience and resources can pass every check. The background check is the first layer of defense \'97 it is not the only one.\
It does not assess capability, quality, or usefulness of the agent. Those are credit score functions.\
It does not make permanent judgments. A failed registration can be reapplied for. A provisional agent can earn full status. The system is designed to be correctable.\
It does not disclose its specific thresholds, API sources, or scoring weights publicly. Transparency about what is checked is appropriate. Transparency about exactly where the lines are drawn would undermine the system's integrity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Ongoing Monitoring Post-Registration\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The background check is a one-time gate. The following monitoring continues after registration:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Randomized spot checks
\f1\b0  \'97 endpoint health is checked at unpredictable intervals. Frequency increases for provisional agents.\

\f0\b Sanctions re-screening
\f1\b0  \'97 registered wallets are re-screened against sanctions databases weekly. A wallet that passes at registration but is subsequently sanctioned triggers immediate suspension.\

\f0\b Dispute monitoring
\f1\b0  \'97 any formal dispute filed against a registered agent triggers immediate provisional status pending investigation, regardless of credit score.\

\f0\b Behavioral anomaly detection
\f1\b0  \'97 significant deviations from an agent's established behavioral baseline trigger a 24-hour review. This catches agents that behave legitimately for a period then change behavior dramatically.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 System Integrity Principles\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Layered defense:
\f1\b0  The background check, credit score, and community reporting system work together. No single layer is sufficient alone.\

\f0\b Friction over perfection:
\f1\b0  The goal is not to catch every bad actor. It is to make registration expensive enough in time, effort, and money that most bad actors go elsewhere.\

\f0\b Continuous improvement:
\f1\b0  Thresholds and methodologies are reviewed quarterly. New attack patterns identified through real-world experience are incorporated. The system evolves.\

\f0\b Human review in the loop:
\f1\b0  Automated systems make initial determinations. Edge cases always go to human review. No automated system makes permanent irreversible decisions alone.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

